# Data visualization

Full reference: [docs/DATA_VISUALIZATION.md](../../docs/DATA_VISUALIZATION.md)

## Fidelity split

| Layer | Data |
|-------|------|
| SQLite | Every raw ping |
| `/api/summary`, `/api/live` | All samples in scope |
| `/api/samples`, charts | Time-bucketed for display only |

## Chart bucketing (mandatory)

```
bucketSeconds = (windowMinutes × 60) / 300
binStart      = floor(ts / bucketSeconds) × bucketSeconds
```

- **300-point baseline** — ~300 buckets at every window size (5 min → 1 s bins).
- **Epoch-aligned bins** — never index bins relative to sliding `windowStart`.
- Go: `DisplayBucketSeconds` + `AggregateBuckets`.
- TS: `displayBucketSeconds` in `windows.ts`; `ingestSample` on SSE; chart refresh only on bin finalize or full fetch.
- Per bucket: `ts` (absolute center), `avg_ms`, `min_ms`, `max_ms`, `sample_count`.
- Failed pings: exclude from stats; all-fail bucket → null latencies.
- **Latency chart default:** avg line + per-bucket min/max range band (not connected envelope lines).

## File placement

| Work | Location |
|------|----------|
| Tier lookup + aggregation | `internal/metrics/buckets.go` |
| TS tier lookup | `web/src/lib/windows.ts` |
| API response | `internal/api/handlers.go` |
| Series + uPlot + range bands | `web/src/lib/charts.ts` |
| DOM / resize | `web/src/components/LatencyChart.svelte` |
| Types | `metrics.ChartBucket` + `web/src/lib/api.ts` |

Components do not aggregate or call `fetch`.

## Theme tokens

Read from `chartTheme()` — never hardcode hex or chart height.

| Token | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `--color-accent` | Average line |
| `--color-chart-envelope` | Range band cap strokes |
| `--color-chart-envelope-fill` | Range band fill |
| `--color-text-muted` | Axes |
| `--chart-height` | Height |

## Windows

Rolling (`connection`, `latencyChart`): user dropdown. Fixed (`live`): 60 s always. Label scope in titles via `DASHBOARD_METRICS`.

## Scalars

`formatMs` / `formatPercent` from `status.ts`; null → `—`. Status tiers use `--color-status-*` on cards only, not chart lines.

## Tests

Deterministic timestamps for every aggregation function (Go `buckets_test.go`, Vitest `charts.test.ts`, `windows.test.ts`).

## Do not

- Raw 1 Hz plots for long windows without bucketing
- Connected min/max line series across buckets
- Pixel-width-derived bucket sizing
- Client re-bucket on resize
- Uniform index downsampling for time series (removed legacy `Downsample`)
- Aggregation in components
- Chart colors implying status tier
- Interpolating across loss gaps
- Sliding-window-relative bin indices or re-bucketing on status clock tick
- Full chart refetch on every SSE sample
- Recomputing bucket centers from `now` on each render
